FBIS4-39893 "drsov113_a_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Reiterates Call for Meeting Reiterates Call for Meeting OW1006134994 Moscow Radio Moscow in Mandarin 1000 GMT 10 Jun 94 OW1006134994 Moscow Radio Moscow Mandarin BFN [Text] Russia still insists that before imposing sanctions against the Democratic People's Republic of Korea [DPRK], an international conference on resolving the nuclear crisis on the Korean peninsula should be convened. Russian Vice Foreign Minister Panov reiterated this view in a meeting with the Chinese ambassador in Moscow on Thursday [9 June]. He had a similar talk with the DPRK ambassador earlier. The idea of calling an international conference was proposed by President Yeltsin, who maintains that North Korea, South Korea, Russia, the U.S., Japan, and China should participate in the conference.
